CRYSTAL LAKE WIND ENERGY I, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Crystal Lake Wind Energy I, LLC ("Crystal Lake I") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Crystal Lake I generating facility ("Crystal Lake I Facility").
Crystal Lake I is a wind turbine generating facility located in Hancock County, Iowa. The Crystal Lake I Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by ITC Midwest, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Crystal Lake I's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Crystal Lake I Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Crystal Lake I's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Crystal Lake I shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $512,418.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $42,701.50.
